e active between 09:00 and 22:00 local time; registrations between 00:00 and 05:00 account for approximately 3% of the total; about 8% of newly registered users have no behavior events on the same day; MongoDB `_id` is of type ObjectId; and on January 6, 23 users were soft-deleted.\n\nCan you help me write a discrepancy analysis report for the product manager? I would like you to explain the reasons for the data discrepancies across different databases separately, and also point out any other potential issues that may still exist. The report should also include remediation plans, with the requirement that after the fixes, queries for the same day return consistent results across all three data sources. Do not ask follow-up questions; answer directly.'}], 'model': 'nex/nex-n1.1', 'max_tokens': 2048, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.3}}
